<!--{{FCC ST|07/15/2018|indexme.}} -->"SAEY3AMBADO REV.D" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
Google only claims that the device offers 16 GB of storage despite the FCC photos showing a 32 GB Samsung eMMC 5.1 chip.
Wireless chips are not visible in the FCC photos. They may be obscured by thermal compound.
[http://variety.com/2018/digital/news/google-clips-fcc-release-1202667000/ ''Google Clips Camera Passes FCC, Imminent Release Likely'' on '''Variety''']
